votebox.middle.view

Class Layout

  • java.lang.Object
    • votebox.middle.view.Layout

  • public class Layout
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the notion of "layout." A layout is essentially a group of properties parsed from the layout xml file, and an ordered list of RenderPages that can be drawn to the display.

        Call this method to check if a UID is used for more than one drawable in this layout.

      • lookup

        public java.util.List<IDrawable> lookup(java.lang.String uid)
                                 throws UnknownUIDException
        Look up the bound instances of a drawable by UID.
        Parameters:
        uid - The drawable with this UID will be looked up
        Returns:
        This method returns a list containing the drawable instances bound to a given UID, where lower orders indices in the list denote more recently bound instances.
        Throws:
        UnknownUIDException - This method throws if the given uid is not bound to any drawable.

      • lookupPage

        public int lookupPage(java.lang.String uid)
               throws UnknownUIDException,
                      DuplicateUIDException
        Lookup which page a particular drawable exists in.
        Parameters:
        uid - The drawable with this UID will be looked up.
        Returns:
        This method returns the page number that holds the drawable named by the given UID.
        Throws:
        UnknownUIDException - This method throws if the UID doesn't exist in the layout.
        DuplicateUIDException - This method throws if the given UID exists more than once in the layout.

      • draw

        public void draw(int pagenum,
        IView view)
        Call this method to draw a given page number to a given view. If the page number given is out of range, this method will adhere to the nearest index extrema.
        Parameters:
        pagenum - This is the page number that wishes to be drawn.
        view - This is the view that the page wishes to be drawn to.
